;; check:fcis allowlist — pre-existing core throws / mutable state.
;;
;; The FC/IS gate (bb check:fcis) bans (throw ...) and mutable state (defonce,
;; atom, swap!, reset!) in core namespaces: core must return typed error values
;; (the shell translates them into HTTP responses) and hold no process state.
;;
;; The namespaces below predate that ban — they are framework-spine code
;; (interceptor engine, validation framework, error-detail construction,
;; pagination/ranking) whose typed throws are precondition/invariant guards
;; caught centrally at the HTTP boundary. They are allowlisted so the gate can
;; enforce the rule for all NEW code while this debt is migrated incrementally.
;;
;; Burn-down tracked in BOU-186 (core/platform infra) and BOU-185 (audience,
;; which is exempted inline via ^:boundary/allow-throw instead). Remove each
;; entry as its namespace is converted to error-return values.
{:allow-throw
 [boundary.core.interceptor
  boundary.core.interceptor-context
  boundary.core.validation.behavior
  boundary.core.validation.generators
  boundary.core.validation.registry
  boundary.core.validation.snapshot
  boundary.platform.core.search.ranking]

 :allow-mutable-state
 [boundary.core.validation.registry]}
